<hl>
<seg id=1> China will continue implementing the financial opening up policy </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Beijing, January 16th, by Xintang Xu and Yuhong Qian- The president of The Bank of China, Xianglong Dai said that, China will continue implementing the financial opening up policy. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> At the news conference to Chinese and overseas reporters today, Xianglong Dai emphasized that, China will not give up carrying on the financial opening up policy because of the financially turbulent situations in some countries of southeast Asia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> He said that, a group of foreign banks and insurance companies set up their brand offices in China last year. By the end of last year, there were more than 170 foreign financial institutes that were set up for businesses in China. </seg>
<seg id=5> In the future, the numbers of branch institutions of foreign banks and insurance companies in China will increase. Meanwhile, the practice of approving foreign banks to provide transactions in RMB will be also extended. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Meanwhile, he also emphasized that, more circumspect management will be taken in the future towards the application of conditions for foreign financial institutes to open businesses in China; the qualifications of their executive officials; and the lawful rights of their businesses. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> He said that, the projects that are using RMB as funds will not be delayed because of the financially turbulent situation in Southeast Asia, and the reason is that there is not a time frame for the currency exchange of RMB. </seg>
<seg id=8> However, in terms of opening up capital projects, Chinese government will draw from lessons learned from the financially turbulent situation in Southeast Asia and proceed with a more cautious attitude. </seg>
</p>
